{
  "stem": "16930.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was either a former big [INAUDIBLE] or former big army place, because it held several hundred boys.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It housed several hundred boys.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and we were like-- like you see-- almost like in-- like you see, like, in the-- the private schools-- you know, in different houses.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The place, it was called Barham House.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The place was called Barham House.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I remember-- while I'm talking to you, I remember it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and-- but it was near a railroad station.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was near-- near Ipswich, which is a big industrial town in the south of England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it received heavy bombings and-- heavy, heavy bombings.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were afraid the kids might get killed, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they evacuated us from this Barham House, this several hundred children, to different places throughout England.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, how long were you at this house [INAUDIBLE]?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Also several months.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not that long.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Refugee-- Jewish refugee children.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whether they were all really Jewish technically, whether-- the Germans didn't go according to-- to Halakha.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They didn't ask are these-- whether the child was a Jewish mother [INAUDIBLE] Halakha.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to be a child according to either grandparents, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Were either their grandparents Jewish?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they were-- Halakhally, there may be a number of kids there which were not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But according to Germans, they were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was a great deal of intermarriage in Germany prior to World War II, prior to the Nazis-- a phenomenal amount of intermarriage, and a phenomenal amount of intermarriage in Austria, and a great deal of assimilation that those kids-- most of them didn't even see themselves as Jewish.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
